abstract.0: A majority of companies now say they have plans for ERP in the cloud, and that means the urgency to make the move is growing. Migrating from on-premises ERP can appear daunting, but the sooner you do it, the sooner you’ll be on an even footing with your competitors. In this session discover ways to simplify your move from Oracle E-Business Suite, Oracle’s PeopleSoft and  JD Edwards, or other on-premises systems. Hear about customers that have made the journey, get expert advice from practitioners, and come away with a better understanding of where to begin.
abstract.1: Powerful new tools are emerging as businesses consume more data in more locations than ever before. Digital transformation requires companies to connect people and integrate resources in entirely new ways. In this session join Digital Realty for a discussion about evolving trends in hybrid cloud and proximity-based interconnection services. Take a closer look at the growing role connectivity is playing in a company’s digital supply chain and discover powerful new resources that can help simplify your path to the cloud, including Digital Realty’s Service Exchange and Connected Campus, while accelerating growth to give you a significant competitive advantage.
abstract.2: A new database architecture called sharding was introduced in Oracle Database 12c R2 for linear scalability and complete fault isolation for OLTP workloads. This sharding architecture horizontally partitions data across discrete Oracle Databases (shards). All shards collectively form a single logical database. Come to this session to learn about this new architecture. Discover Oracle Sharding through the proof of concept project: see what type of application best fits the sharding architecture, how to deploy a sharded database, and how to implement replications for massive scalability and complete fault isolation on commodity hardware with local storage.
abstract.3: Agilab is an ISV offering Agilab Science as a SaaS solution. In this session learn how it migrated from Amazon to Oracle Cloud and cut costs due to the multinenancy possibility with Oracle PaaS and greatly improved performance. Hear how Agilab is implementing Oracle Analytics Cloud to its SaaS solution to address the business needs of its customers, and is also working on a common go-to-market with an Oracle Life Sciences solution to increase its business and Oracle revenue.
abstract.4: As you plan for your future data management and analytics strategy, the cloud will certainly play a crucial role in any path you follow.  It’s no longer a question of if but when, and for many, the when is NOW. In this session discover the five paths to the cloud that will influence how you architect and deploy analytics at any scale across cloud, on-premises, and hybrid deployments. By choosing the appropriate starting point on your journey to the cloud, based on your own unique requirements and company policies, you can take best advantage of all the benefits that cloud architecture and subscription economics have to offer.
abstract.5: In this session learn about an audience-first marketing strategy and how to drive efficiencies across your marketing teams through the Oracle Data Cloud platform. Think broader than media by expanding this planning strategy to other teams in your organization such as analytics, email, search, social, and TV.
abstract.6: Asset servicers typically have large volumes of complex terms and conditions contained within their fee schedules. Translating these terms and conditions can be a time-consuming and labor-intensive manual process prone to errors. These errors translate into incorrect fee calculations and invoices leading to loss of revenue and customers. This session explores how to implement Oracle Revenue Management and Billing as a single global pricing and calculation system that can automate and streamline your fee schedule data entry, all within a project with a positive ROI.
abstract.7: Oracle and Infosys, a global Cloud Elite member of Oracle Partner Network, launched an automotive cloud solution for fleet distributors and automotive dealerships as a complete and integrated offering built on the Oracle Cloud platform by leveraging PaaS and SCOR to meet specific industry requirements.  The solution is designed to increase supply chain performance on a single, unified platform for both vehicles and aftermarket business. The solution enables enterprises to transform into an agile enterprise, automate manufacturing processes, improve financial forecast accuracy with predictable revenue planning, increase warehouse efficiencies by delivering increased automation, and improve supply planning accuracy. Attend this session to learn more.
abstract.8: Whether you are steering into the cloud or looking to digitally transform your business, this session offers the best practices and Oracle solutions required to meet your needs now and in the future. Learn about the capability that Oracle has to meet the needs of automotive suppliers and understand the roadmap for the future. As automotive supplier, this session is sure to help you understand things you can do now to better prepare for a successful digital future.
abstract.9: The world of indirect tax is changing with many countries adopting digitalization and advanced automated tax reporting that is leaving no room for mistakes in VAT, GST, or sales and use tax returns. The Tax Compliance Manager is a PaaS solution built on Oracle Application Express utilizing Oracle Cloud technology that helps keep your costs to a minimum but maximizes your tax capabilities for the most accurate VAT analytics available. This session explores the power of using Oracle PaaS and how you can have seamless integration with your Oracle ERP and cloud applications.
abstract.10: Moving your supply chain management solutions from on-premises to the cloud creates a wealth of new possibilities.  As customers make this transition they often ask how they can do so most effectively.  In this session learn practical best practices for migrating supply chain management to the cloud based on your starting on-premises landscape, be it Oracle E-Business Suite, Oracle’s PeopleSoft or JD Edwards, or a third-party legacy application. The session includes case study examples from customers that have undertaken the journey to the cloud, and the benefits they have realized.
abstract.11: Finance and HR provide the operational business foundation for organizations. Yet for many businesses this foundation is fragmented and not built for speed, insight, and ultimately business outcomes. In this session learn how organizations can gain operational efficiency and agility by having finance and HR working together.
abstract.12: In the next evolution of digital transformation, the enterprise of tomorrow has to transcend functional and siloed systems to ensure the success of the entire business with connected outcomes. This session picks some common business challenges and demonstrates how to effectively solve them by integrating the front- and back-office technologies.
abstract.13: Whether you're simulating automotive crashes or discovering new medicine, Oracle Cloud Infrastructure  can help you with full end-to-end solutions that allow you to scale with various tools and pipeline infrastructure. You can run compute-intensive workloads and then view results in a virtual desktop infrastructure and workstation offering on Oracle Cloud Infrastructure. In this session hear about the new high-performance computing and compute-intensive instance offerings that provide an industry-first RDMA capability.
abstract.14: Delivering innovative business transformation while living in a world of increased regulatory compliance of personally identifiable information, and the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)—Oh My! This session draws back the curtain on the technology that enables the business use cases for big data: innovation, customer insight, operational efficiency, fraud, risk, and compliance. It examines real-world examples of each use case and the technical architecture that supports them.
abstract.15: You hear about blockchain, IoT, and artificial intelligence at every turn, but how much is hype and how much is real?  These technologies offer the potential to fundamentally alter the arc of business, jobs, and society at large. Blockchain offers the promise of increased trust and accountability; IoT enables unprecedented connectivity between devices, machines, and people; and artificial intelligence delivers prediction with precision. In this session explore the impact of these exciting technologies for businesses and learn about their value to enterprise applications. You will also hear about customers that are using blockchain, IoT, and AI to transform their businesses today.
abstract.16: In today’s ever-changing dynamic and complex business environment, transaction processing requirements, reconciliation, and reporting elements have increased significantly. These, coupled with a heterogeneous landscape either by choice or design, potentially increase the cost of processing and quality of data. In this session hear how Cognizant is leading customers toward a digitally driven, modern finance organization by leveraging Oracle ERP Cloud and Oracle EPM Cloud applications supported with bots and Blockchain. Learn from SMEs from Cognizant and Oracle on how Oracle Cloud applications have the capability to create the next-generation finance organization.
abstract.17: The rapid provisioning of dev/test and production environments is essential in modern IT because it enables an agile and robust DevOps pipeline and operation. For organizations to excel, they need to release new applications quickly and efficiently. In this session learn how to transform your current environment into an agile DevOps platform using complete infrastructure, database, middleware, Oracle Applications Unlimited, and industry solutions. Oracle Advanced Customer Services has the expertise and tools to help customers rapidly adopt, execute, and manage their DevOps practices on cloud or on-premises platforms. Join this session to see Oracle Advanced Customer Services DevOps platform services and tools in action.
abstract.18: Every business is a software business. More and more customers want to consume software as a service. If these statements are true for your business, it is more important than ever to understand the capabilities and tools required to run efficient, high-scale SaaS. In this session walk through those capabilities, including physical regions and compliance, foundational compute and storage, deployment and orchestration, and edge services and security. Walk away with a better sense of a modern approach to building and running a SaaS offering.
abstract.19: Software development companies need virtual environments for dev/test, UAT/testing, sales demos, customer PoCs, security testing, end-user training. System integrators also need virtual environments for integration projects. The transient demand for such environments doesn’t justify building data center capacity. Join this session to learn how to configure and run these environments with “data-center-like” environments (including the ability to run VMware VMs with layer 2 networking) on Oracle Cloud Infrastructure Ravello Service. This session also demonstrates how the Ravello development team drinks its own champagne by using Ravello for continuous integration to create/deploy environments in the cloud for integration testing several times a day.
abstract.20: In the modern digital economy, customers’ expectations are changing as Millennials lead the way in using mobile apps for banking, retail, and other consumer transactions. Companies need to adapt quickly to this new paradigm to stay relevant and grow their customer base. In this session learn about an innovative approach to building industry solutions leveraging Oracle Cloud Platform, and see a demonstration of a retail solution built on a number of Oracle PaaS technologies including intelligent assistant, machine learning, and augmented reality.
abstract.21: While financial business metrics lead the way when considering a move to the cloud, reimagining how work gets done beyond the technology is vital as well. After the technology selection and implementation, it’s important to establish the mechanisms to measure value realization on the investment and build a governance model for sustainability going forward—connecting the project to positive organizational outcomes and long-term success. In this session gain perspective from Creighton University on how to begin an HCM cloud journey with the end in mind. Learn the importance of setting up the justification for your investment, and then building the support structure and service models to ensure a return on your investment.
abstract.22: Public transport companies have a wealth of information they could leverage to improve the travel experience of their customers. Information such as schedules, real-time data about the buses and journeys, and details about tickets can all be of interest for travelers. Connexxion used Oracle Mobile Cloud Service to expose this information by offering APIs that can be used by mobile applications in different contexts. This opened a new channel of business partners: companies that offer door-to-door mobility services and resell the bus tickets in their mobile application. In this session learn how using Oracle Mobile Cloud Service helped Connexxion to go live with the platform in less than nine months with a complete solution.
abstract.23: As commercial  banking clients take their business to the cloud, Citi is actively pursuing partnerships to simplify the process for clients to connect to Citi. The main objective of the partnership with Oracle is to enhance client experience by removing friction in the onboarding process and allow Oracle ERP customers to directly connect to Citi. The joint solution on Oracle Cloud Marketplace and Oracle’s Digital Innovation Platform is the result of a partnership between Citi and Oracle with a goal of simplifying treasury operations. During this session learn how new  ecosystems are being formed across large banks and technology giants to deliver value to joint customers.
abstract.24: Citi’s enterprise supply chain is partnering with Citi trade and treasury services and Amazon Business to streamline procurement of nonstrategic spend within the Oracle platform. The benefit of this program includes automated payment processing through Citi virtual cards, supplier rationalization and risk reduction, enhanced data reporting and analytics, invoice reduction, consolidated tax information, potential elimination of catalogs, supplier diversity tracking and reporting, one-stop shopping from multiple sellers, and buying desk purchase optimization. Attend this session to learn more.
abstract.25: Connecting physicians to patients in remote locations for diagnoses and monitoring with the same clinical accuracy of an in-hospital exam can reduce readmission rates and cost, while increasing patient satisfaction. In this session learn how Oracle is being leveraged as part of a set of case studies to enable connected care and remote patient monitoring across the globe.
abstract.26: In this session learn how you can leverage Oracle Internet of Things Cloud Service in conjunction with Oracle Transportation Management Cloud Service to address common challenges faced when managing your fleet such as controlling fuel spend, efficient dispatch and routing, real-time vehicle location, accurate estimates for time of arrival, and monitoring driver behavior.  The session also explores how to reduce costs and improve vehicle utilization through IoT-enabled fleet maintenance.
abstract.27: There has been a steady evolution in performance management practices over the last several years, with organizations moving from the traditional practice of evaluations once or twice a year to a more ongoing approach. The focus is on frequent, active dialogue between the employee and manager with more emphasis on coaching and development and looking forward, less emphasis on past performance and ratings. In this session explore some of the flavors of continuous performance management and discuss how Oracle supports them with Oracle HCM Cloud’s talent management solution.
abstract.28: The pace of change is accelerating faster than ever before, affecting the way business is  done and organizations are run. The role of HR is having to adapt, transform, and utilize technology to compete for talent, engage the workforce, and develop leaders for tomorrow. In this session explore the transformative nature of today’s workforce while examining the role of emerging technologies in the future. Get a peek into the future of technology and how AI and chatbots will help you unleash the power of your people.
abstract.29: In today's environment, financial institutions face the challenge of creating incremental growth in both the top-line revenue and in profitability. This is especially true within a low-growth environment where operating model changes are approached cautiously and disruptive technologies may be viewed as a threat. Traditional methods of performance measures alone will not provide insights for decision-making. In this session explore how data can be the unifying factor in joining both operational and performance measures to drive risk and financial outcomes and enable fact-based decision-making. Hear a banker's perspective on how to modernize a profitability framework and measurement platform.
abstract.30: Rendering houses have produced hundreds of minutes of top-quality 3D animation and visual effects in HD for film, TV, computer games, commercials, and mobile apps. These range from high-end commercials for brand name clients such as Cartoon Film, NBC, Cisco, SyFy Channel, Verizon, National Lottery, and Orange, to drama hits. In this session learn how the media houses use Oracle Cloud Infrastructure to render these movies while bursting onto the cloud to gain significant advantage over their competition.
abstract.31: In this panel session learn from the experiences of customers that are using Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud to drive their businesses, make the right decisions, and find hidden information. The panel conversation will be wide-ranging, with customers from a variety of industries around the world discussing their business and technical challenges, reasons for choosing Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud, experiences and benefits gained, and future directions.
abstract.32: Data is everywhere these days and it’s likely, as a marketer, that you do—or will—use it regularly. But what do you do if you never quite learned the data basics? Don’t worry, you won’t be called out; this session is here to help. Oracle Data Cloud’s data lab is on a mission to educate and empower agencies and brands to understand data so you can connect more deeply with your customers. In this session learn terms you need to know, see real-world examples, and discover the next steps for you to begin utilizing in your marketing strategies. Tune into this 101 training session to get a thorough introduction on how to navigate in this ever-changing ecosystem.
abstract.33: The newly introduced Oracle Sharding feature promises horizontal scalability and higher availability for relational applications. However, success or failure in designing and running a sharded application depends on understanding sharding principles and adapting the application to use the right data model. Based on considerable shared experiences with designing, developing, and maintaining sharded applications, this session explores how to qualify and design applications that use the new Oracle Sharding feature.
abstract.34: The current state of marketing to small and midsize businesses (SMBs) is both complex and expensive. But it doesn't have to be. Announcing Oracle Data Cloud's new SMB marketing product, which uses innovative data capabilities to reach SMBs in any vertical, across all major digital activation channels. This session explores how marketers can leverage this product to achieve higher coverage across their SMB customer base, with more account-based marketing style targeting of SMBs at scale. Learn how the solution complements SMB marketing with other account-based marketing and channel marketing programs.
abstract.35: Tech startups can't afford DBAs, and they don't have time to provision servers and scale them up and down or deal with patches or downtime. They've never heard of indexes and they need data loaded and ready for analysis in days, not months. In this session learn how Oracle Database developers can build data warehouses as a hip startup data engineer would—but using a proper database built on Oracle technology. Oracle Data Visualization Desktop provides analytics and data exploration with techniques explained in this session. Hear real-world development experiences from working on data and analytics projects at a tech startup in the UK.
abstract.36: Since Oracle announced support for some of its products on Docker there has been a flood of posts on Oracle blogs about Docker, but very few seem to tackle the hard questions. This session takes a look at Docker from a DBA perspective, demonstrating what it does well, and more importantly what it doesn't.
abstract.37: As with machine learning, deep learning is often quoted but less often understood. In this session get a layman’s view of deep learning. This won’t make you a data scientist, but it will help you understand the basics. Get an overview of the underlying techniques, learn how neural networks operate, see some of the deep learning frameworks, and dive into some use cases of deploying the technology.
abstract.38: The highly regulated life sciences and healthcare industry sectors pose unique and complex requirements for contacts, billing, pricing, claims, chargebacks, and rebates, but the profitability of the business is tightly knit with these processes. With the migration to SaaS at the forefront of CIO objectives, the demand for a streamlined revenue management and billing solution has grown exponentially. This session demystifies complex, sector-based requirements and provides an overview of both cloud and hybrid solutions based on market analysis, and also includes specifics on the Oracle Cloud solution. The analysis includes market trends for outsourcing versus in-house business processes and impacts to the bottom line.
abstract.39: A successful collections digitization strategy needs to combine three critical elements: sophisticated segmentation, digital self-service, and borrower centricity. Join this session to learn how Oracle Banking Collections helps you succeed in the digital world.
abstract.40: The high tech industry is leading change as startups are quickly disrupting industries as diverse as automotive, industrial, banking, hospitality, and transportation. As the industry evolves, mergers, acquisitions, and newly initiated startups are changing the world. High tech companies must rapidly embrace new technologies to remain competitive or risk becoming obsolete. In this session learn how companies are embracing the cloud and emerging technologies such as IoT, artificial intelligence, and Blockchain to meet the needs of today and the future. Hear examples of where new technologies are transforming the way companies compete and prepare for the future.
abstract.41: Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud brings enormous benefits in database management and operational efficiency. This approach allows you to focus your resources on strategic applications and business initiatives. In this session learn how to prepare your database environments for fast Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud onboarding. Gain insights into how Oracle Advanced Customer Services can provide tailored support to help with the integration of Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud and management of your hybrid database environments.
abstract.42: The supply chain—more than any other ERP siloes—is uniquely in the leading position to benefit from disruptive technologies. How has disruptive technologies such as  IoT, AI, and Blockchain transformed the supply chain? In this session hear and see how these disruptive technologies have helped enterprises grow, reduce cost, and make better use of existing assets.
abstract.43: Data storage efficiency and performance are key success drivers for any enterprise computing environment. In this session learn engineering insights, best practices, and real-world customer use cases for a cost-effective data protection solution that provides both efficient data reduction and optimized backup and recovery performance for your enterprise environment.
abstract.44: This session is directed at the CIO and the IT professional who is being asked to architect a machine learning platform. As demands for machine learning use cases have grown across nearly every organization, it has become increasingly challenging for IT leaders to support these use cases in an efficient and scalable manner. Tasks such as provisioning resources, building environments, and managing deployments are taking up too much support hours and preventing organizations from developing scalable workflows for building and deploying AI solutions. In this session learn how the Oracle’s data science platform can make data science workflows more self-service, and help IT teams better support growing data science teams and use cases.
abstract.45: In this session explore the challenges faced by an auto component distributor trying to ensure visibility of inventory across supply chain partners, rapid order fulfillment, cost reduction, and transactions including POS data. Learn how to address these issues with Oracle ERP Cloud and Oracle Blockchain Cloud Service, which provide a platform for data availability across partners. See how the solution enables sharing of inventory views across partners, and maintains POS reporting traceability and product information across lifecycle, ensuring timely inventory fulfillment and replenishment and quicker financial settlements.
abstract.46: Extend the reach of your custom and packaged applications beyond organizational or departmental silos by integrating with a Blockchain network for single source or truth and trusted business transactions across enterprise boundaries. In this session learn different approaches and best practices for integrating custom applications, such as those built on Oracle Tuxedo or Oracle WebLogic, and packaged ERP systems, such as Oracle E-Business Suite, to interact with other systems through Blockchain transactions. Learn how to enable your current enterprise systems of record to start transacting on a Blockchain network and how Oracle is extending its comprehensive suite of applications leveraging Blockchain.
abstract.47: Extreme finance is Oracle’s vision for how finance organizations can use technology to drive extreme business performance using technology to work smarter, not just harder. In this session see examples of how technology is reshaping the work of finance. Learn about innovative analytics and embedded machine learning, see how to act faster through automation and a cloud platform for scenario analysis and business modelling, and discover how to perform richer analysis by considering all relevant data, not just data in your ERP. Come away with a firm understanding about how technology can truly transform finance.
abstract.48: Cloud computing is transforming business practices and simplifying data center operations. However, when it comes to moving critical database assets to the cloud, many IT leaders are leery—and rightly so. They have seen the limitations of popular commodity cloud solutions, which mostly consist of fragmented hardware and software offerings that must be manually configured. Can a public cloud offer turnkey database functionality along with the high levels of security, availability, scalability, and performance that you are accustomed to in your own data center? With Oracle Cloud the answer is yes. Attend this session and discover what Oracle Database Cloud can do for your business.
abstract.49: We asked executives from more than 100 organizations why they needed analytics. They said, "To make the right decision and to drive a behavior." Finding the right insight to make the right decision is becoming harder yet more important than ever. In this session learn how Oracle Analytics Cloud is helping Oracle HR leaders use varied data sources, domain knowledge, artificial intelligence, and customer feedback loops to surface the right insights, enabling business leaders to collaborate and make winning decisions. The right data. The right decisions. The right time.
abstract.50: Do you have the visibility, insight, and knowledge you need to effectively align software investments with your business strategy, now and for the long term? What does it mean to be smarter about your software so you can better manage change and strengthen competitive advantage? In this session get an introduction to the transformative approach behind Oracle’s new software investment advisory (SIA) organization. Learn how SIA invests in your success with tailored solutions and industry best practices for optimizing your Oracle environment across cloud, hybrid, and on-premises environments.
abstract.51: It is hard to make intelligent business decisions when you only have partial facts. Learn how a complete, future-proof, and trusted cloud can transform your business now and into the future. In this session see how Oracle’s SaaS suite can offer your customers an even better customer experience by giving them what they want in real time, and offering them what they don't even know they need yet, all via easy-to-use Oracle AI and Oracle IoT solutions. See how existing customers are using Oracle Cloud applications to create a connected intelligent business.
abstract.52: The energy industry today faces significant change in an evolving landscape of the distribution world. Driven by the convergence of increasing distributed energy resource deployments and customer/regulatory expectations of safe, reliable, and affordable power delivery, utilities must adapt with new advanced distribution management and planning applications. To succeed, a solid data management foundation is essential. Based on direct experience with utilities and tool vendors, this session explores how to develop the practical knowledge, guidelines, and experience to build and maintain accurate up-to-date grid models that can be used enterprisewide to manage an increasingly dynamic grid.
abstract.53: With more than 7,500 FinTech firms around the world raising nearly US$110 billion in capital, the FinTech digital revolution is well underway. However, many of these firms will likely not succeed because of their inability to achieve the right product/market fit, overcome the high cost of attaining scale, or find and align with the right partners. In this session learn how Oracle helps enterprise-class FinTech firms accelerate their path to digitization and monetization, driving innovative solutions in areas such as biometrics, payments, discovering Blockchain networks, Blockchain and Oracle ERP  integrated trade/working capital management, and artificial intelligence.
abstract.54: Digital marketing to small and midsize businesses (SMBs) requires a strategic approach customized to distinct objectives, needs, and buying cycles. How can data enable you to create an effective marketing strategy that will maximize your reach to SMBs and drive results for your organization? If you’re a B2B marketer focused on reaching SMBs, join this session to hear from Oracle Data Cloud and a panel of experts on how applying data-driven strategies can transform your SMB marketing across digital platforms.
abstract.55: In this session learn how to enable on-demand Oracle Network Cloud Service – FastConnect access using the world’s first elastic SDN, powered by Megaport. Gain direct connectivity into Oracle Cloud, giving you access to self-provision and connect networks securely using a reliable low-latency network with guaranteed throughput. Using a next-generation web portal by Megaport, you can deploy real-time connectivity for virtual routing and flexible bandwidth for private cloud-to-cloud, multicloud, and hybrid solutions. Watch Megaport and SmartDog demonstrate these abilities to handle data replication, migrations, backups, VM builds, and disaster recovery strategies.
abstract.56: This session focuses on how business leaders can help their organizations better compete with artificial intelligence. While AI capabilities have become a “must have” for enterprises, many struggle with realizing value from their investments. These challenges go beyond hiring the right talent, they involve developing the tools, technology, and techniques needed to become an algorithm-driven company. In this session learn how your organization can identify gaps in its capabilities and develop strategies to deliver more value with artificial intelligence. Walk through how Oracle’s data science solutions can serve as a cornerstone for the development, deployment, and management of AI solutions.
abstract.57: What are the logical steps for federal, state, and local government; higher education; and healthcare entities to successfully plan and prepare to move to Oracle Cloud?  During this session experts from Oracle Consulting’s Public Sector team present best practices for successful migration from on-premises environments to Oracle Cloud, including selecting a use case, creating a change management strategy, and developing an architecture for the future of the cloud. Examples are grounded in real-life, actual consulting engagements that showcase the importance of a holistic and strategic approach to people, processes, and technology for your move to Oracle Cloud.
abstract.58: Financial services firms know all too well how regulatory compliance and accounting standards are taking up too much valuable time that could be spent on analysis and review to help drive the business.  Add data quality and governance into the mix and now regulatory spend overpowers running the business. In this session learn how technology has helped one financial institution drive its compliance spend with holistic regulatory reporting and data governance initiatives. Learn how this firm reduced time to submission, increased its ability to do analysis and review cycles, and optimized usage of its data assets.
abstract.59: Baleno is a bakery company that wanted to expand its business all over Egypt. It needed an agile solution to provide availability for all of its branches but couldn’t purchase a server for each branch or create a consolidated data center. The economic situation in Egypt means companies in Egypt can’t make big investments in IT. In this session learn what the company did to provide an effective solution that enabled it to start small and expand when needed.
abstract.60: In this session the Oracle ACE team again takes on the challenge of a live poly-cloud demo. This time the focus is on microservices architecture and Oracle’s PaaS cloud services that support microservices. Microservices architecture promises flexibility, scalability, and optimal use of compute resources. Through independent components and a well-defined scope and responsibility, interface, and ownership that are evolved and managed in an automated DevOps process, this architecture leverages current technologies and lessons learned. See it live with Oracle Cloud Infrastructure Container Service Classic, Kubernetes, Wercker, event hub, DBaaS, Oracle API Platform Cloud Service, data hub, Oracle Visual Builder Cloud Service, Fn project, and Oracle JavaScript Extension Toolkit.
abstract.61: ERP data is complex and when several ERP systems are involved, the complexity increases exponentially. In this session learn how a Fortune 50 company designed a modern finance data lake for general ledger and finance transaction analysis on data in multiple ERPs, enabling users to experience instant query response across vast and varied data. In this session learn how applications including Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Edition, Tableau, and custom executive dashboards all connect to Sparkline and consume data in seconds. See how to leverage Spark, Sparkline, and in-memory modern OLAP cubes/indexes for ERP/general ledger data analytics at scale.
abstract.62: Bloom Energy has complex supply chain planning requirements due to the nature of its product, procurement processes, and global manufacturing operations. In this session hear how Bloom implemented Oracle ERP and supply chain management products including supply and demand planning in the cloud. The planning implementation required multiple plans in sequence including application extensions in PaaS to run material allocations using custom engineering logic. Bloom used safety stocks, alternate BOMs (product structures), phantoms, and multilevel/multiorg product explosion, and complex sourcing scenarios to plan the manufacturing supply chain. Bloom also used consigned, virtual machine interface, and min/max planning to augment material requirements planning, adding to the complexity.
abstract.63: First introduced in February 2014, Oracle EPM Cloud has grown significantly in solution footprint as well as customer adoption, and now offers a complete set of proven EPM capabilities in the cloud, deployed by several thousand global customers.  But moving to the cloud is not about simply lifting and shifting capabilities from on-premises to the cloud; it’s an opportunity to reinvent and transform your business processes and infuse them with best practices and emerging technologies. Attend this session to learn about companies that have successfully migrated from Oracle Hyperion to Oracle EPM Cloud to transform business processes within and beyond finance.
abstract.64: Come join this interactive session and see how Oracle Manufacturing Cloud, in partnerships with leading-edge international industrial companies such as South Korean Bistel, German Bosch Rexroth, and Japanese Mitsubishi Electric, can help transform your manufacturing operations. Learn how these combined solutions can help enable your manufacturing operations to become more flexible, automated, and efficient. Regardless of how your operations are performing today, be prepared to come away with ideas on how you can improve for the future.
abstract.65: Oracle's License Management Services offers a fundamental re-evaluation of how Oracle's audit process unfolds. From initial contact through closure, Oracle is actively talking with customers to find ways to drive improvements and give them a more proactive voice in helping shape Oracle's future focus and strategy.Oracle is are committed to changing the type of conversations being held across the audit process. In this session learn how Oracle's License Management Services is putting the customer front and center to transform and improve the audit experience.
abstract.66: The pace of evolution in consumer markets has dramatically accelerated, primarily driven by an increasingly sophisticated and better-connected consumer. Significant innovation is taking place in retail and direct-to-consumer through experimentation with technologies including AR/VR, AI, ML, Blockchain, IoT, and robotics. Although many retail practices remain relevant, disrupters and early adopters are putting pressure on traditionally run businesses. If change is constant, it’s never been more so than now. In this session hear stories and lessons of companies that are taking necessary risks and consequentially delivering unique experiences and value to shoppers who are being enticed and coming back for more.
abstract.67: What will be the catalyst for the next industrial revolution? GE has placed bets on additive manufacturing. GE Additives is changing how manufacturing is done today and in the future with new technologies, while meeting new regulatory requirements. GE Additives’ innovative manufacturing processes require an unprecedented level of integration and visibility across the supply chain. To support these needs and the digitization of the business, it chose Oracle Cloud solutions to provide visibility into its value chain, and PwC to architect the supply chain design and guide the overall business transformation. Attend this session to learn more.
abstract.68: Corporations are demanding new products from banks that support their cash and credit management strategies. For corporate customers, immediate access to the right credit and loan information throughout their business cycle has become all the more important. Virtual accounts eliminate the need to maintain numerous physical accounts while providing an effective alternative to managing accounting/cash management structures. The combination of Oracle solutions for credit, cash, and liquidity management offers banks unsurpassed digital capabilities. Join this session to learn about Oracle's new solutions for corporate banking.
abstract.69: Are you worried about a lack of alignment between your company’s overall strategic plan and daily operations? Do you struggle with overall supply chain visibility and execution, or optimizing resources to maximize profitability? Do you or your corporate executives stay awake at night worrying about incorporating digital, real-time market and demand signals for better supply chain management?  If so, come see how Oracle Cloud can help enable a fully integrated end-to-end business planning process. This session includes a live demo that that explores ways to help you better align your supply chain operations to your business strategy. Plan to walk away with concrete ideas to help transform your business.
abstract.70: Fake news. Controversial content. Ad blocking and fast forward. A world where automation, programmatic buying, new technologies, and a rapid evolution of digital advertising outlets means you’re losing control of where/how/when customers view your ads. What can you do to ensure your brand’s health and protection? Looking inward, you need to be sure that your brand is one publishers want to align with—and be sure you’re with a publisher you should align with. Even more important is the outside view. It’s critical that your brand is building the goodwill and trust among customers’ ever-growing skepticism. In this session hear a discussion around this highly charged issue that tech has created, and get tips on how to combat it.
abstract.71: Are you moving to the cloud? Looking at containers? Keeping some workload on-premises? Shifting workloads from on-premises to the cloud, and from the cloud to on-premises? Maybe splitting workloads between the two into a hybrid cloud? If you said yes to any of these, you are not alone. In this session see how Kubernetes can be used to run cloud-native and existing workloads both in Oracle Cloud and on-premises on Oracle Cloud at Customer. See how customers are using both use cases.
abstract.72: Many large and small manufacturing companies deploy Lean Manufacturing techniques requiring scalable and flexible solutions to support agility and growth. In this session learn about Oracle’s approach to providing enterprise applications in the cloud while enabling your facilities to run lean. See how Oracle can help you simplify your manufacturing processes, improve efficiencies, execute takt-time scheduling, and improve your business and supply chain planning processes. This session also includes an integrated demonstration showing how you can leverage takt-time scheduling to improve your lean operations.
abstract.73: In this session learn how organizations in Latin America (from Mexico down to Argentina) are complying with the local requirements established by the local statutory department. For instance, Latin America is becoming a world leader in the use of e-invoicing as governments spearhead the drive to reduce tax evasion through real-time invoice validation. Quite a few countries—and the list is growing—have legislated electronic accounting rules that impact how charts of account are managed, as well as accounting records and transactions in your ERP.
abstract.74: Given its clear benefits and countless use cases, it’s no wonder intelligent automation has become a mission-critical initiative. This new wave of  technologies has the power to increase enterprises’ speed, scale, quality, and precision. It also can drive never-before-seen levels of operational efficiency, and both complement and augment human skills. The race is on to develop an intelligent automation strategy. Are you considering a takeoff—or already in flight? You know embarking on such a broad and important digital transformation project is no time to throw caution to the wind. Attend this session for tips on getting started, leveraging preconfigured bot libraries for Oracle, and getting your automation program cleared for takeoff.
abstract.75: Enterprise applications thrive in high-performance and low-latency environments. With Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, Oracle Applications run in their natural habitat: a cloud built by Oracle, optimized for mission-critical applications, and Oracle workloads. With Oracle Premier Support, you get seamless support and security you can rely on with flexibility on where you run prod, dev, and test environments. Because you bring both your apps and business customizations to the cloud, users have the same experience and the same comprehensive support. In this session learn how you can take advantage of the inherent benefits of Oracle’s IaaS platform’s and hear how customers transformed their business by moving their core applications to Oracle Cloud Infrastructure.
abstract.76: Lifting and shifting your enterprise workloads to Oracle Cloud’s infrastructure as a service (IaaS) is the best and fastest way to make your organization more robust to market changes. This is exactly what a global leader of water services did by moving its JD Edwards workload from on-premises to Oracle IaaS. Attend this session to learn more.
abstract.77: Hear from the experts about how to leverage the benefits of Oracle technology while maximizing your investment in the Oracle Cloud at Customer suite, including Oracle Cloud at Customer, Oracle Exadata Cloud at Customer, and Oracle Big Data Cloud at Customer. In this session see Oracle Cloud at Customer use cases and discuss how this platform can help your business. Discover how Oracle Advanced Customer Services can help jumpstart your organization’s transition and efficiently manage your workloads in the Oracle Cloud at Customer environment.
abstract.78: The value of a platform is in the solutions it enables and how it helps customers rapidly build and deploy them to drive business value. Oracle Blockchain Cloud Service is dedicated to simplifying and accelerating Blockchain adoption in the enterprise. This session showcases customer and partner solutions in financial services, supply chain, and other verticals and explains how customers identify applications suitable to enterprise Blockchain and apply design methodology to define distributed applications. Hear about real-world applications using Oracle Blockchain Cloud Service and get a view on how Oracle is helping make Blockchain a reality in the enterprise.
abstract.79: Integrating Oracle EPM Cloud to Oracle’s JD Edwards solutions enables organizations to be better informed, leaner, more agile, and link operational and strategic performance metrics. In this session see the business case that a JD Edwards client made for the solution as well as integration options, the importance of the right implementation plan, and how Oracle EPM Cloud can reduce planning and budgeting cycles, improve forecast accuracy, enable better capital management, and shrink losses. See how to successfully implement and unlock this powerful and profitable tool for the organization.
abstract.80: How do you protect your organization from greedy cyber criminals, malicious insiders, and rogue nation states? Your ERP system contains extremely sensitive data and essential business processes, so its security is mission-critical. The threat landscape is rapidly evolving in complexity, and finance, HR, and supply chain leaders must be diligent in defense. Attend this session to learn about how to use KPMG’s controls-in-depth principles to dramatically reduce risk and cyber exposure. Discover how to deploy Oracle’s cybersecurity and risk management capabilities and products to manage and automate your risk mitigation programs in a cost-effective manner.
abstract.81: In this session learn why Oracle ZFS Storage Appliance is uniquely positioned to serve as backup and data storage for Oracle's engineered systems. With a DRAM-driven architecture and support for high-speed network interconnectivity, it can offer extreme I/O performance for backup and restore speeds. With integrated support for Oracle Hybrid Columnar Compression and uniquely coengineered features including Direct NFS Client, Oracle Intelligent Storage Protocol, and industry-acclaimed DTrace analytics, Oracle ZFS Storage Appliance is ideally suited for Oracle Database workloads both on-premises and in the cloud.
abstract.82: If your business model is B2B, it’s very likely that you leverage direct marketing and work with an ecosystem of partners that sell your products and services. Your marketing efforts may require reaching target accounts, channel partners, and small, medium, and enterprise business prospects. Oracle’s full-suite data capabilities for marketing and advertising technologies now enable you to introduce data-driven insights in your planning, tactics, and execution aligned to your business goals. In this session industry experts share best practices for maximizing your investments across account-based marketing, small and midsize business, and channel marketing programs.
abstract.83: In this session learn lessons, tricks, and tips from NTT DATA’s implementation of Oracle HCM Cloud for a large client with 5,000 employees in 72 countries. Hear about the complexities of working with independent global decentralized HR departments in multiple georegions while moving to a centralized cloud solution. Gain fresh insight into the art and science of moving to the cloud at this level of complexity and why it's important to have a trusted advisor along on your journey.
abstract.84: Enabling customers to easily move their Oracle workloads to the cloud is an important factor for helping them be successful. For Oracle Databases, however, this poses some explicit challenges, such as managing different versions and different functionalities. Because all databases in the cloud are encrypted, there are challenges when wanting to simply move their data to the cloud. This session highlights Oracle Cloud Infrastructure Database and provides tips and best practices.
abstract.85: Business leaders and CXOs are facing a new reality that is defined by skyrocketing expectations and accelerating, unpredictable change. This session provides insights to help you navigate this constant state of flux, chart your own course, and futureproof your business. Hear from Qatar Navigation (Milaha), one of the largest maritime and logistics companies in the Middle East, on its selection of Oracle ERP Cloud to replace Oracle E-Business Suite.
abstract.86: The life sciences sector has become increasingly demanding, with medicines and supplies needed quickly. Although technology has made this possible, customer fulfillment is still an area that needs much improvement. An efficient warehouse management system that works seamlessly across inbound processing, inventory management, and outbound processing is the key. In this session explore distribution strategies and operational and fulfillment challenges. See how gaining a complete view of current business processes and requirements for growth ensures strategic advantage.
abstract.87: Provisioning the hardware and software needed to develop and deploy machine learning neural networks and applications can be an arduous task, requiring hundreds of pages of arcane documentation. Data scientists need to focus their time and effort on machine learning, not software and hardware installation, configuration, optimization, deployment, version reconciliation, and systems admin. With additional leaps in capability every year from hardware manufacturers, there is also a need for constant innovation on the cloud providers in the hardware space. In this session learn how Oracle Cloud Infrastructure is removing these barriers by innovating on cutting-edge hardware to make it simpler for users to deploy frameworks and other components.
abstract.88: Biopharma firms are driven by high standards of quality compliance and governance such as FDA regulations. The potential for recalling products that contain contaminated, noncompliant, or improperly labeled ingredients has risen as the complexity of drug manufacturing has increased. When manufacturers sell products to customers or vendors, the ability to track the raw material and product and shipment information is important. In this session learn about a track and trace solution that provides improved cGMP regulatory compliance, material tracking and recall, recall responsiveness cost, FDA good practice safety regulation compliance, enterprisewide traceability for quality analysis, and risk reduction on public health and brand image.
abstract.89: The world is changing, and the workforce of the future will be very different than it is today. Driven by accelerating connectivity, new talent models, and cognitive tools, even the work itself is changing. In this session explore the latest human capital trends and their potential impact on the future of work.
abstract.90: Improving business agility and moving to flexible and scalable architecture does not need to be a hard problem to solve any more. Migration to Oracle Cloud is made easy with IBM Migration Factory and Migration Services. Migrating to a cloud platform opens up doors to immense digital innovation. In this session learn how IBM is helping clients get more out of their Oracle’s JD Edwards ERP applications by converting them to systems of innovation with robotic processing automation, chatbots, IoT, and cognitive solutions.
abstract.91: With supply chains continuously changing and becoming more complex, logistics and distribution networks need to be more agile and have the ability to store and ship products and materials on a global scale. In this session learn how Oracle Logistics Cloud enables customers to unify their logistics and supply chain execution systems and processes, allowing them to improve global visibility, optimize operations, orchestrate processes in a coordinated manner, and achieve better business outcomes.
abstract.92: In this session learn about enhance business processes, collaboration, and business transactions between enterprises through decentralized shared digital ledgers and Blockchain technology. Blockchain technology brings unprecedented reliability, integrity, nonrepudiation, accuracy, efficiency, and immutability to shared data and transactions, allowing business to be conducted in a secure, reliable, timely, trusted, and auditable environment between diverse enterprises. Learn how Oracle Consulting is working with Oracle Product Management to leverage this disruptive technology in order to help customers create new and innovative revenue streams while impacting the future of process collaboration, data exchange, trust, and transactions.
abstract.93: Cloud computing offers many benefits including increased scalability, flexibility, availability, and productivity. While cloud computing shares similarities with other service delivery models such as managed services, cloud computing also offers its own unique opportunities and complexities. In this session learn how Oracle Advanced Customer Services can transition your systems to an Oracle Cloud IaaS environment and manage your systems there. Oracle Advanced Customer Services has a holistic and pragmatic approach to cloud adoption with custom-developed tools and experience-based expertise. Join this session to learn more about the benefits of leveraging Oracle Advanced Customer Services to ensure the success of your cloud journey.
abstract.94: Database security is important to understand and implement to ensure data protection from insider and external threats. It is vital to make sure that data is secure in the cloud and in transit. There are options and products available in Oracle Cloud that can be utilized, and DBAs and security professionals should understand these tools. This session is focused on security in Oracle Cloud and including this in an overall security posture.
abstract.95: It’s inevitable that your business strategy, models, growth, people, financials, etc. are consistently changing.  It’s hard to stay on top of these changes and realign your business as it happens. Oracle Enterprise Data Management Cloud Service has arrived (a new tool modeled after its on-premises version, Oracle Data Relationship Management) to help standardize dimensions, hierarchies, attributes, and mapping maintenance across the enterprise.  Adventist Health is one of the first adopters of this tool.  In this session hear its story and why it chose Oracle Enterprise Data Management Cloud Service for data governance, collaboration, and master data management across applications.
abstract.96: Hear Oracle's IT leaders share how Oracle transformed its own global US$37 billion business to run on Oracle ERP Cloud. The session also covers the implementation strategy and recommendations based on lessons learned to those who are starting this journey.
abstract.97: In this session hear Oracle's IT leaders discuss how Oracle modernized HR functions for its 140,000 employees on Oracle HCM Cloud. The session also covers the implementation strategy and recommendations based on lessons learned for those who are starting this journey.
abstract.98:
Join us for the 5th annual Oracle License Management Services “Unplugged” session at Oracle OpenWorld. This is an exclusive opportunity for Oracle customers to hear the latest license management news and ask questions of the experts. Topics covered include licensing in hybrid cloud/on-premises environments, virtualization, and tooling/measurement. Plus, learn from the experiences of other Oracle customers about best practices for working with Oracle License Management Services and managing software, database, and hardware licenses.

When: Monday, Oct. 22, 2018, 10:00 AM - 1:00 PM (networking lunch included)
Location: The Palace Hotel, Sea Cliff Room, 2 New Montgomery Street
abstract.99: Oracle Sales Cloud is a powerful SaaS application, and Oracle's PaaS cloud extends SaaS dramatically.  In this session learn how Oracle used PaaS to build an Oracle JavaScript Extension Toolkit single-page Oracle Sales Cloud app for its 10,000-strong inside sales force, which increased CRM adoption by more than 100x in a single year.
abstract.100: In this session learn the details of Oracle's hardware supply chain transformation and how it ensured engineering, planning, and execution for all organizations. In this effort, Oracle moved all supply chain business functions and processes including planning, product design and development, master product information, manufacturing, costing and quality, global fulfillment, financial orchestration, and source-to-settle flow to the cloud, using the Oracle SCM Cloud suite of products.
abstract.101: Learn how Oracle became one of the largest organizations in the world running all its key business applications in the cloud. In this session hear how Oracle leveraged the power of integrated cloud services across SaaS, PaaS, and IaaS to power digital transformations that enabled the company to modernize its business practices.
abstract.102: In this session hear about the evolution of SaaS support and discover Oracle’s game-changing SaaS support services model that was built on customer feedback. Get a firsthand look at how Oracle is raising the bar for SaaS customers by providing them with a platinum level of support service and offering them advanced support options to tailor their services to align with their objectives. Hear from customers that have been a part of the Voice of the Customer program from the beginning and have been instrumental in helping Oracle build a support offering that is turning the SaaS industry on its head.
abstract.103: Payments transformation with the customer at the center is the new normal. For example, the impact of real-time payments has been profound, from enhancing cash management capabilities to improving the overall efficiency of operations. Banking customers are increasingly demanding more such impactful transformations. Globally, clearing and settlement systems are gearing up to meet this challenge, with banks not far behind on the adoption curve. Tangible changes are underway, beginning with rapid transaction origination, message transformation, and committing transactions. Attend this session to learn how one customer has successfully transformed its payments business.
abstract.104: Digital origination is table stakes for today’s banks, as customers today are likely to start their purchasing journey digitally. It includes even researching and evaluating products. Banks who create poor first impressions with irrelevant product suggestions, bad user experience and unnecessary charges cannot be a preferred banking partner. Discover how banks can move beyond just selling and create trust and value necessary for customer retention. Reinvent customer experiences by putting customer at the heart of the origination process. Given the requirements of a digital customer, learn how banks must respond and adapt by redesigning some operations, processes and capabilities from front to back end.
abstract.105: Fast, ad-tech streaming data lands in a data lake. Consuming this enormous volume of data and deriving timely insights is a challenge. And designing a consumption layer that meets the needs of various business users adds another level of challenge. In this session a leading ad-tech company outlines how it approached and solved the problem and achieved very fast responses for applications and dashboards, through in-memory indexing.
abstract.106: Going beyond the AI hype, the session discusses in detail some common uses cases of AI in customer experience specifically for marketing, sales, and commerce. Learn how practical and real-life business use cases in customer experience can be solved with AI.
abstract.107: In this session learn how advanced HCM controls enable you to assess, communicate, and analyze the security information needed for GDPR and sensitive data protection. Hear from experts on best practices for GDPR programs and embedded tools to automate and simplify compliance tasks.
abstract.108: In this session learn how  to assess, communicate, and analyze the security information needed for General Data Protection Regulation and sensitive data protection. Hear from experts on best practices for GDPR programs and embedded tools to automate and simplify compliance tasks.
abstract.109: Data security, integrity, privacy, and compliance with regulatory requirements are a top priority for most companies no matter if they run their databases and applications in their own data centers or on cloud platforms. Today, organizations are challenged to address security requirements while also running and growing their businesses.  In this session hear from the experts on how to securely transition critical business applications and protect sensitive data when moving to Oracle Cloud. Learn how Oracle Managed Security services can help you achieve and maintain compliance, better manage users and roles, and secure access to your on-premises and cloud services while saving time and money.
abstract.110: Combining Oracle Cloud with Oracle Database Appliance can provide high-performing, redundant, high-availability, real-world hybrid cloud solutions. In this session explore real customer needs to minimize cost while bridging the gap into the world of cloud. The session includes deep dive discussions of Oracle Cloud backup, hybrid cloud disaster recovery, license structures, patching, implementation strategies, and subscription models, as well as lessons learned during actual customer implementations.
abstract.111: RE/MAX is a leading US real estate services company with a network of independent realtors. The company had been using spreadsheets to track accruals for advertising spend, which was resulting in high costs, risk to the organization, and financial errors due to manual processes. RE/MAX partnered with Oracle Applications Consulting to deploy Oracle Procurement Cloud and Oracle Purchasing Cloud to maintain its advertising spend information. In this session learn how RE/MAX used Oracle Procurement Cloud and Oracle Purchasing Cloud to significantly improve business processes, resulting in increased productivity and financial compliance, reduced costs, and an improvement in cash flow forecast for overall advertising spend.
abstract.112: Customers today consider the availability of banking services across all digital channels a “must have,” delivered least intrusively, most valued. To achieve this banks need to move out of the regular banking ecosystem, embrace open banking, and reach customers across segments. In this session learn how Oracle Banking Digital Experience and Oracle Banking APIs enable banks to accelerate their open banking journey, provide customers with a seamless banking experience, and do more than just comply with regulations.
abstract.113: With the release of Oracle Mobile Cloud Enterprise, customers now have the ability to enhance the user experience and provide connected relevant content instantly. Through modern mobile applications that are easier to create and intelligent chatbots that provide a conversational interface, employees can escape the daily drag of navigating through a poor interface to try and find relevant content. Come to this session to hear more about how deploying a connected chatbot army can help your users get to the information they need to do their jobs effectively across applications and business processes.
abstract.114: Is access to your cloud and on-premises business applications secure? Do you have the resources, expertise, and infrastructure to implement your IT modernization programs and automate account/privilege management and attestation? Join this session to learn about Oracle Managed Identity Cloud Service, powered by modern and time-tested identity and access management (IAM) technology. This end-to-end service frees you from infrastructure and software management, monitoring, and upgrades. Hear from experts how Oracle Managed Identity Cloud Services can save you time and money, and lower your risks while providing identity and access management solutions tailored to your specific needs.
abstract.115: Critical success factors for managing data storage in a global economy include applying intelligent and scalable solutions for multisystem data management and monitoring. In this session learn how to leverage simple REST instructions and apply log mining techniques to simplify enterprisewide data storage management.
abstract.116: Financial systems are evolving rapidly and finance teams now have the opportunity to uncover insights and drive efficiencies that can move the enterprise forward. In this session explore the six digital disrupters that leading organizations are using to create business value. Learn how Deloitte’s Finance in a Digital World offering combined with the power of Oracle Financials Cloud can help organizations put these disrupters to work. See how you can explore massive amounts of information to drive insights, reduce costs, increase efficiency, and reduce risk all while enabling value creation across the entire enterprise.
abstract.117: What’s keeping you from the cloud? Fear of a long, expensive migration process? Worries over internal resource requirements? Difficulty making a business case? Did you know that you can upgrade to the cloud in 20 weeks and reduce costs by 30 percent? Have you seen the mobile-friendly app that guides and measures your upgrade progress with transparency and ease? It’s a whole new world with Oracle Consulting. In this session learn how you can reduce costs, increase efficiency, and boost revenue with SOAR, Oracle’s automated cloud upgrade offering. Let us focus on the technology so you can focus on your business and join some of the world’s biggest and best organizations in the cloud.
abstract.118: Solairus Aviation manages, operates, and maintains business jets for Fortune 500 companies and ultra-high net worth individuals.  At Oracle OpenWorld 2014, Solairus CFO Mark Dennen laid out a vision of providing Solairus customers with a transparent view of the financial and operational information about the management of their aircraft. Solairus chose Oracle Fusion as an ERP/PPM foundation to provide a scalable product it would never outgrow.  In this session learn why Solairus integrated different Oracle PaaS and IaaS products with Oracle Fusion to complete the vision.
abstract.119: As many as 50 billion devices will be connected by 2020, and businesses are looking to gain value out of better predictive models. In this session learn how data science helps you take action on these devices supported by IoT, big data, and analytics platforms.
abstract.120: Attention is a scarce resource. This is why intense debates have emerged over how to keep consumers engaged, including the merits of short-form video over long-form and even how to measure engagement. Attention is the fundamental core of what all creators of digital content—from publishers, to advertisers to platforms and beyond—are seeking. Viewability and humanity are prerequisites to meaningful engagement and measured attention, but these are just the beginning. As attention paid across digital channels continues to evolve, so too must the way the industry transacts and uses data to inform creativity. In this session learn about a new paradigm for measurement and explore how to leverage information for media and creative decisions.
abstract.121: High-performance computing, AI, 3D rendering and visualization, and many traditional enterprise applications require a level of peak performance and predictability that has traditionally been difficult to emulate in the public cloud. So often organizations feel they must make sacrifices to move these workloads to the cloud. No longer. Oracle Cloud Infrastructure provides all the traditional benefits of IaaS—pay-as-you-go, fast provisioning, scalability—but also offers many of the benefits found on-premises, such as granular visibility and consistent high performance. In this session learn how Oracle Cloud Infrastructure can help you run performance-intensive applications by providing equal or better performance, predictability, and consistency than most dedicated, on-premises environments.
abstract.122: You’ve already been convinced that the time to move to the cloud is now. You’ve rallied your organization around the idea of moving to the cloud, yet you’re unsure of what to do next. In this session learn how to approach the challenge of moving to the cloud. Hear stories and lessons learned from those that have already done it and ultimately walk away one step closer and clearer to how to begin your cloud transformation journey.
abstract.123: In this session learn about the three big NOs of Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud: no human labor, no human error, and no manual performance tuning. Equipped with Oracle Database 18c, the next generation of the world’s #1 database, Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud offers total automation based on machine learning and eliminates human labor, human error, and manual tuning. See how in addition to all this it is also super fast compared to everything else.
abstract.124: SaaS is a great way to run your business with industry-leading software but without the pain and expense of maintaining the applications or data center. Cloud applications do not typically sit in isolation and frequently integrate with many other cloud workloads and on-premises applications via application programming interfaces or extensions on PaaS and IaaS. How does your business proactively monitor and manage these integrations and extensions to minimize the impact of ongoing change? In this session learn how Oracle Advanced Customer Services SaaS experts have helped customers successfully manage and monitor SaaS integrations and extensions and how these services can help you deliver increased value to your business.
abstract.125: Artificial intelligence is top of mind for many marketers and is a growing trend. How can AI process thousands and millions of data points in a split second to automate smarter decisions? Is now the right time to start adding AI capabilities to the mix? In this session learn how Oracle’s AI apps amplify the capabilities within B2B and B2C marketing to improve customer experience, engagement, and conversion.
abstract.126: In this session see how Oracle ERP Cloud and Oracle EPM Cloud are driving increased productivity and how finance teams can position their companies to take advantage of the huge opportunities that emerging technologies offer. New research from the Warton School predicts the US GDP could grow by $2 trillion over the next 10 years—with the productivity boom being powered by emerging technologies such as AI, machine learning, IoT, and the cloud services that deliver them. Hear from National Rural Utilities Cooperative Finance Corporation, learn why CFOs are poised to lead this growth, and see how you can position your company to get ahead of the future of finance and realize tomorrow’s finance, today.
abstract.127: In this session learn about Aker BP´s journey to move its Oracle Databases to Oracle Exadata and Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud. Aker BP was one of the first Beta customers of Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud and could experience the excellence of that product from the very beginning. Hear about the complete process of uploading data to the object store, creating and migrating the database schema, and finally loading the data into Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud. This session also explores the Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud administration console and using the AI interface with Jupiter Notebook technology.
abstract.128: When it comes to integrating, securing, and efficiently managing your IT architecture, a common challenge today is the complexity of a hybrid, multicloud environment. With some legacy systems on-premises, best of breed SaaS applications running in their own clouds, and new cloud native applications spread across multiple cloud vendors, many organizations struggle to efficiently and effectively manage across these silos. Attend this session to hear about best practices and tools for intelligently integrating, managing, analyzing and protecting your business when it’s spread across multiple data centers and cloud silos.
abstract.129: The expanding digital world of "smart" connected devices, AI, and Blockchain are fast becoming the norm. As consumers rapidly adopt the latest in personal digital assistants, wearables, and data-producing devices, government agencies are beginning to implement new technologies to rapidly respond to some of the most pressing issues of today. In this session explore how AI, Blockchain, and IoT can shape the future of how government agencies provide services to citizens. This can include deploying virtual assistants and robots that give instant access to city services, using Blockchain to establish trust and leverage data collected with IoT sensors, and integrated city systems to drive efficiencies.
abstract.130: In this session get market perspective and essential guidance for the technology buyer about how the cloud is accelerating the adoption of Linux. Get an overview of the commercial Linux market from a data center and cloud perspective, learn about the buyer journey in the digital economy, and see why the right type of operating system is crucial for this journey. Additional topics include the importance of a business-ready and battle-tested Linux platform for mission-critical workloads on-premises and in the public cloud. Discover how you can optimize your infrastructure environment today with Oracle Linux to get ready for migrating to cloud environment in the future.
abstract.131: To meet line-of-business demands and forward-leaning IT, a new wave of cloud application projects is underway. The pressure to quickly bring applications and infrastructure to market are forcing many organizations into high-paced lift-and-shift programs that can outpace the ability of security to keep up.  This so called “pace gap” is creating opportunities for increased risk, decreased visibility into transactions, malicious behaviors, fraud, and abuse. In this session hear from the senior editors/contributors to the Oracle and KPMG Cloud Threat Report and gain perspectives on what this survey of 450 global respondents says about the state of cloud security.
abstract.132: We are living in the early days of the fourth industrial revolution, as shown by advances in exponential digital technologies such as robotic process automation, cognitive computing, and Blockchain, and this digital disruption is impacting every facet of an enterprise. CFOs and the finance organization can either help drive this digital agenda or be left behind. With Oracle Cloud, the agility of the finance function can be increased by appropriately identifying and deploying digital enablers. In this session learn how this new class of digital disruptors is transforming how the work of finance gets done.
abstract.133: Migrating to the cloud should not be a nightmare. It can be an easy process that is not much different that any on-premises migration. In this session learn from three cloud migrations successfully completed last year. The case studies include migrating to the cloud from bare metal and virtual environments, and a migration that required near-zero downtime. This session provides all the knowledge you need to start today on your own migration to the cloud.
abstract.134: To successfully address rapidly evolving talent marketplace, escalating recruitment costs and increasing employee turnover, HR teams need to swiftly evolve their strategies and technologies. The newly announced integrations between LinkedIn and Oracle HCM Cloud and Taleo Enterprise Edition enables HR teams to take a holistic view of their talent’s experience, skills and career aspirations in order to grow their talent pool, improve the candidate experience and enhance internal mobility. Come to this session to hear about the key trends in the workplace that informed the expanded LinkedIn and Oracle partnership, the details of the newly announced integrations, and the benefit it will bring to HR and recruiting professionals.
abstract.135: Microservices can help teams bring change with more speed and agility, but success requires more than new architecture.
