Technical professionals responsible for application architecture must also drive a DevOps culture and changes in process, organization, and platform to deliver business benefits. This session covers how microservices and DevOps with Oracle Cloud help organizations maximize agility and return on investment on the journey to IT modernization.
abstract.136: They came to the cloud for the cost savings, but they stay for the innovation. That’s the key finding of a new survey of organizations that have implemented cloud ERP and EPM systems. The ability to stay current on the latest technology and best practices ranked #1 on the list of benefits. In this session learn how take advantage of tomorrow’s ERP to innovate today and predict tomorrow. Hear how companies are using the latest emerging technologies and innovations to build the business of the future. And come away with a vision of where your business needs to go to compete, grow, and thrive.
abstract.137: New technologies continue to disrupt the customer relationship management space. In this session learn how technology trends including chatbots, artificial intelligence, and event-based architectures are driving the future of customer experience and what you need to do as a business to stay ahead of the curve.
abstract.138: The goal in most enterprises is to design and build a unified database infrastructure that serves various workload demands. The design should also take into account how the organization plans to expand its data analytics, from data warehouses to data lakes. In this session learn how Lenovo and Oracle, working together, have delivered a unified architecture to serve both transactional and data warehouse workloads and have laid the foundation for implementing data lakes for an end-to-end data flow model. Get a detailed overview of the architecture and configuration of the solutions and discover the best practices learned through customer installations.
abstract.139: Managing data resources on a global scale is a key component of a successful data management strategy. In this session learn engineering insights and best practices for managing data in a global name space as well as securely migrating and transforming data resources without impact to data availability.
abstract.140: Transitioning to a digital world means engaging with customers when they choose through their preferred channel, and a set of simplified yet very nuanced services. This transition will touch every part of a service provider organization and their partners. Performance in customer satisfaction and efficiency will be measured on a new set of metrics and targets. This is more than a process change or data migration. It is a complete change in operational model. At the same time, this transition provides a fantastic opportunity to reshape customer behavior, shed legacy products and services that are no longer competitive, and create new revenue streams. In this session hear how Oracle Communications Consulting has guided customers through this journey.
abstract.141: In contrast to the linear economy, the circular economy does not see an absolute end to a product or process. Instead, this closed-loop economic system offers companies and society the chance to manufacture, use, and reuse genuinely sustainable products. The distributed ledger technology Blockchain is one important technology that can support the necessary digitization of value creation networks. In this session learn how to leverage game-changing technologies to secure a sustainable world for future generations. Go beyond the hype and see how Blockchain can be turned into a value-creating and trust-increasing business reality and be utilized to unleash the full potential of the digital circular economy.
abstract.142: This session introduces business analysts to key data science concepts needed for audit and security analysis.  Learn how to create audit algorithms with easy-to-use graphical tools that embed data science techniques such as anomaly detection, clustering, fuzzy matching, and so on to stop fraud and strengthen security.
abstract.143: Oracle Database 18c comes with many new and exciting machine learning algorithms. This session explores these new features and presents live demonstrations of how to use them to gain deeper insights into your customer data.  In addition to the in-database deep learning feature, this session also examines how additional deep learning can be embedded into the database using the R extensibility framework.  Using RESTful services learn how you can now bring deep machine learning to developers, enabling them to build advanced applications utilizing the power of Oracle Database in the cloud.
abstract.144: It is becoming increasingly difficult to decipher, analyze, and implement regulatory mandates and disclosures; interpretations vary, and given the frequency, volume, and impact of changes, keeping pace is effort-intensive. Financial institutions spend billions of dollars every year attempting to streamline their regulatory efforts and seek a solution to help reduce this effort.  Attend this session to learn how your organization can benefit from Oracle's efforts at continuous compliance with applicable regulations aided by machine learning and artificial intelligence while reducing resources.
abstract.145: What migration path to Oracle Cloud is right for you? In this session learn about the three distinct paths to cloud migration from the Oracle Cloud experts, Oracle Consulting.  1. Get started in the cloud with rapid start services for fast, easy, and value-priced migration. 2) Accelerate to the cloud by moving workloads to the cloud through prebuilt automation in the Oracle Consulting studio. 3) Extend the cloud with services that optimize and maximize your Oracle investment. This session provides best practices, lessons learned, and frameworks to accelerate your cloud implementation success.
abstract.146: Are you still running your business-critical Oracle Applications on-premises? The time is right to move them to the cloud. With Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, your apps will be running in their natural habitat: a cloud built by Oracle that is optimized for Oracle workloads. In this session learn how moving these apps to Oracle's cloud will help your organization innovate faster, improve availability and reliability, and reduce costs. Get practical insights from solution experts and customers that have recently made the move. Learn how easy it is to make the move with professional services from Oracle and an ecosystem of experienced third-party MSPs that are invested in your success.
abstract.147: Today’s global supply chain is very complex and there is limited visibility and transparency among supply chain partners distributed across the globe. The regulatory and compliance requirements are country-specific, transaction costs are high, and any compliance violation may have financial and company image consequences. In this session learn how Oracle’s digital supply chain solutions with Blockchain can help you transform your supply chain. The session highlights Oracle Blockchain Cloud Service features, integration with Oracle applications, and a demonstration of business use cases including smart contracts.
abstract.148: The new-age business challenges affecting the manufacturing industry today—such as increasing market volatility, shorter product lifecycles, higher product complexity, and adoption of global supply chains—are necessitating the implementation of new-age technologies. There is no single solution that can help manufacturing companies migrate to Industry 4.0 to deliver business outcomes. This involves a combination of multiple technologies and frameworks to achieve digital transformation of the entire value chain. Wipro’s Intelligent Factory Solution powered by Cisco and Oracle simplifies this complexity, integrating IT, OT, and IoT under one umbrella and helps accelerate the move towards a digital enterprise. Attend this session to learn more.
abstract.149: This session explores the future of the Oracle Cloud Platform and the value it adds to your business. The range of capabilities across all Oracle Cloud Platform services (data management, application development, mobile, AI and bots, application and data integration, analytics, security, and management) will help your organization lower cost, reduce risk, accelerate innovation, and get predictive insights. Join us to learn more about this vision.
abstract.150: In this ever-changing business environment, companies are continuously looking to reduce cost while increasing revenue and productivity. Join this session to hear Hearst and Willis Towers Watson describe how it deployed Oracle's cloud technology and its plans for incorporating analytics, intelligence, and automation. The session also explores how the company is evaluating its operating model and skillset to achieve the vision and business case associated with its finance transformation objectives. Join Accenture, along with executives from Hearst and Willis Towers Watson, in this engaging session.

BrainPlow Founder, Serial Entrepreneur, Performance Technologist, Oracle ACE Director, Award-Winning Author, Speaker, Community Organizer, Dad of 4 Awesome Kids. 

Oracle ACE Director Tariq Farooq is an Oracle Technologist/Architect and has been working with various Oracle Technologies for 25+ years at some of the world's largest organizations. He is an award-winning Speaker, Author, Forumizer, Blogger & active Community Leader/Organizer. He was the founding president of the IOUG Cloud Computing SIG. He is the founder of www.brainSurface.com, a Social Networking & IT Collaboration site with thousands of signed-up users for the various Oracle Communities. He founded, organized and chaired various conferences including VirtaThon, the largest online-only conference for the various Oracle domains, the CloudaThon & RACaThon series of conferences and, the first ever Oracle-centric conference at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) in 2011. Tariq was the founder and anchor/show-host of the VirtaThon Internet Radio series program. Tariq is an Oracle RAC Certified Expert, holds a total of 14 professional Oracle Certifications and, is the author of 100+ oracle-centric articles, white papers & other publications. Tariq has presented/spoken at almost every major Oracle conference/event all over the world including Oracle Open World, COLLABORATE, RMOUG, BrainSurface, VirtaThon, OTN, IOUG, OAUG, OOUG, UKOUG, OUGLC, INSYNC, DB Tech Showcase, ACOUG, TCOUG, & many others. 4.bio:
John Hagerty brings more than 35 years of expertise in business analytics and enterprise technologies and applications to his role of VP, Product Strategy for Oracle’s Analytics portfolio.  
Prior to joining Oracle, John was VP and Distinguished Analyst at Gartner, the IT research firm.  An analyst for a total of 16 years, he advised companies of all sizes and in all sectors globally regarding technology options, deployment best practices, governance and collaboration strategies as well as optimal cloud and hybrid architectures for business intelligence, analytics, and performance management applications. John recently published Gartner’s “2017 Planning Guide for Data and Analytics” and has been the lead author for Gartner’s Magic Quadrant for Business Intelligence and Analytics Platforms in the past. 
John also took a two year break from Gartner from 2012-2014 and joined IBM as Program Director for Big Data & Analytics.  In that capacity, he was an external spokesman for the IBM portfolio, created and managed sales plays/program execution, and developed overarching messaging for industry analysts and customers/prospects.

24.bio:
Guillermo currently heads up the Purchase to Pay Global Process Owner Team responsible for the standardization and optimization of global processes for over 95+ countries, to include the implementation of core and disruptive technologies. 

Guillermo joined Citigroup Procurement Services in June 1999 as a Program Manager responsible for procurement of Global Logistics, Relocation Services, Expatriate Services, Credit Bureaus and Record Retention.  In 2005, he was named LATAM Region Procurement Head and was responsible for the region until the integration with Banamex in early 2007.

From 2007 through 2010, Guillermo created and headed the Procurement Service Delivery Team, responsible for aligning the strategic objectives of our internal business customers with the delivery of procurement services. He also assumed Global Category Lead responsibilities for Facilities. In 2011, he worked in strategic planning and execution focusing on the LATAM/Mexico Region reorganization and the implementation of the Procure-to-Pay (P2P) tool.

 In February 2013, in addition to his on-going responsibilities, he worked on key expense reduction initiatives in Central America and was appointed acting Procurement Cluster Head for CCA. Guillermo also assumed responsibility for leading the LATAM Region Reengineering Team and Risk & Control Function.  

Prior to Citigroup, Guillermo worked for United Parcel Service (UPS) for 11 years, holding positions in several areas of management to include marketing, finance, sales and operations. He was part of a team that opened 42 operations in 27 countries with his last assignment as Director of Operations UPS Logistics Group-Latin America Region.

Guillermo holds an undergraduate degree in Aerospace Engineering from the New York University Tandon School of Engineering and an MBA in International Business from the University of Miami. He was also commissioned in the US Army as an Infantry Officer and was stationed in Fort Bragg, NC and Fort Benning, GA.

25.bio:
Dr. Jonathan Baugh is originally from a small southern Utah town where he was active in academics, sports, and outdoor activities. Dr. Baugh attended the University of Utah in Salt Lake City, where he earned his Bachelor’s Degree in Biology and a minor in Chemistry.  Dr. Baugh attended medical school at Edward Via Virginia College of Osteopathic Medicine (VCOM at Virginia Tech). 
Following medical school Dr. Baugh spent his internship in St. Petersburg, Florida. Dr. Baugh then moved his family to Kingman, Arizona where he completed his Emergency Medicine residency. Dr. Baugh has worked in numerous Emergency Departments and has served as the Facility Medical Director twice and been on the Medical Executive Committee and other boards several additional times at several hospitals. Dr. Baugh currently is employed at Dixie Regional Medical Center, which is a Level II trauma center in St. George, Utah. He and Adam Hardage, started Remote Health Solutions, a telemedicine company with an emphasis in technology that allows medical access to corporate, military, airline, remote and austere environments. 
Though all this time Dr. Baugh has valued education and has several publications and exhibits that have included novel device design, patents, and national awards.
Most importantly, Dr. Baugh has been an active member of his own family, church, and community, holding numerous volunteer and leadership callings, including boy scouts and volunteer medical service.

39.bio:
Dominic Cugini is the Transformation Executive for the Consumer Lending Servicing and Default Management program at KeyBank. The group’s focus is to transform our consumer lending servicing technology ecosystem and streamline our operational processes. This will improve our ability to adapt to market changes with speed, improving our future ability to provide an improved client experience, reduce our inherent risk and allow our teams to focus on value-added tasks.

Our mission: To improve our client and employee experience by simplifying our consumer servicing and default interactions with Key, through leveraging out of the box solutions and industry best practice. This will result in more efficient and effective operational processes, an improved risk and control environment and create a framework for client self service capabilities.

Dominic joined Key in 2006 and has held several leadership positions, most recently as the Director and SVP of Quality Assurance Services within KTO. Prior to KeyBank, Dominic held various leadership positions at National City Bank and Metro Media Technologies. He is active in Key’s commitment to the community, as demonstrated through his continued volunteer work with the Business Volunteer Unlimited, Cleveland United Way and the Summit County Board of Health.

Dominic Cugini grew up in Richfield, OH, and is a graduate of Revere High School. He has a Business Management degree from John Carroll University and is a Lean Six Sigma Black Belt.  Dominic and his wife, Melissa, reside in Richfield and enjoy hiking, yoga and golf.

Arnab Banerjee is a Principal Consultant with Enterprise Applications Services of Infosys Ltd. He consults in the area of ERP and Blockchain for Supply Chain Domain. His consulting experience of more than 16 years spans across North America, Europe and Asia. In his blockchain consulting role he helps develop blockchain use cases and implement solution on blockchain products. His research interests include information technology and blockchain applications in supply chain management. He has extensive publications in the area of reverse supply chain, lean/agile/leagile initiatives, theory of constraints, supply chain transformations and humanitarian logistics. Over the years he has published more than 12 research papers in various peer reviewed international journals. He has to his credit eight international conference research
papers, three case studies, and two book chapters. He has published Point of View documents, White Papers and blogs on Oracle products based on his Blockchain Technology experience and researches which he does while doing his consulting assignments. His blockchain publications are well read and widely regarded across the board. He holds a PhD in Supply Chain Management, a Master’s in Industrial Engineering and a graduate degree in Mechanical Engineering. He is a certified Six Sigma black belt champion. He is listed in Who’s Who of the World 2015 edition.

52.bio:
Randy Rhodes is a Technical Executive at the Electric Power Research Institute, where he leads collaborative research projects with the enterprise architecture team within the Power Delivery and Utilization business unit. Randy's current research is focused on next-generation applications for integrating renewable energy sources with the grid.  

Randy has four decades of experience in the electric utility sector, as a utility employee, consultant, and industry research analyst. His utility experience includes grid system planning processes and modeling experience, and he has championed a model-driven enterprise integration approach for the last two decades. His served as Utility Co-chair for the Common Information Model Users Group, supporting the development of network modeling standards. While a Research Director at Gartner, he interacted with hundreds of utilities and dozens of vendors around the world. He has published over 100 research documents covering advanced distribution management systems, geographic information systems, standards-based integration, and the business strategies necessary to develop a digital grid.

59.bio:
Mostafa Gado is the CIO of Jico and a freelance web developer.
He was hired by Baleno - a Coffee shop franchise - on January 2015 to build a software for handling day to day operations. Back then there were only three Baleno branches.
Because of the rapid growth of Baleno and the many offers they received to manage other franchises and projects, the founder of Baleno Ahmed Osama started Jico as a mother company for Baleno and more projects to come.
Jico is a project management company that is specialized in managing coffee shops and restaurants and soon hotels.
Today Jico is managing 14 Baleno branches and a new three branch coffee shop franchise named Tota Capanna owned by the Security Directorate of Hurghada.
Because of the rapid growth of Jico, the first application Mostafa has developed using Oracle Forms and Reports was not enough. Specially that the entire app and the database was deployed on each branch's POS machine.
He found that they now need a more modern, agile and centralized system to handle Jico's growth.
With a combination of Oracle Application Development Framework and Oracle cloud infrastructure he was able to build an ERP system worthy of Jico's ambition.

64.bio:
Vice President, Global Head IOT/Digital transformation for Industry 4.0 , Oracle 
Eric Prévost has 20 years of experience working in digital and business innovation, and transformation strategy roles. He has deep cross-industries knowledge in innovation practice, Digital/Business Strategy, Design Thinking - Customer eXperience, Supply Chain, Service, IOT and Industry 4.0 areas. His career experience includes senior and executive positions in management and IT strategy at IBM Global Services, Capgemini and Oracle.
In Prévost’s current role within Oracle’s Industries Solution Group, he leads digital transformation and IOT initiatives for Automotive, Industrial Manufacturing and Aerospace & Defense industries, with numerous innovative project successes in Europe, South-Korean and Japan.
 
Prior to this role, Prévost was innovation director and head of the business/IT innovation consulting team in the Capgemini Manufacturing business unit. He successfully supported manufacturing companies in their innovative transformation strategy and implementation to the services and pay per use-based business model. Prévost also worked in the roles of CIO and head of Enterprise Architecture with numerous IBM’s customers in the healthcare, banking, manufacturing and public sectors, helping them successfully implement new IT organizations and IT transformation roadmaps for supporting business and digital. 

Prévost also serves as the BPM France Practice Leader at Capgemini; co-authored “BPM: Modeling through Monitoring”, an IBM book; co-authored an Industry 4.0 whitepaper from French Syntec, and authored several papers on BPM and innovation practices for business.

Prévost is also president of the TRIZ-France innovation association in charge of developing innovation practices in France and worldwide innovation cooperation. He is an active member of the French Alliance of the Industry of the Future, and an active member of the Industry 4.0 working group at Syntec Numerique, the first Digital Professional French Association.

66.bio:
C. Prasanna Venkatesan is currently Director, Digital / IoT Industry Solutions in Oracle’s Industry Solutions Group. He brings a wealth of experience in building Internet of Things (IoT) solutions across multiple industries for the better part of a decade.  

Prasanna has 15 years of experience from Engineering to Management Consulting and Business Development. Prior to Oracle, Prasanna led solution management and business development for Cisco's IoT industry vertical solutions group, focusing on Energy, Process and Manufacturing Industry customers. He was among the early members of Cisco’s IoT business unit, where he helped plan and execute the GTM for its first set of products and solutions.   

Prior to Cisco, Prasanna was with Management Consulting firm A.T. Kearney in Chicago, where he consulted for clients in the Telecom, Manufacturing and Energy sectors. Among his other roles, he has worked for Cummins Engine Company, Citigroup and The Asian Development Bank.  

Prasanna holds a bachelors in engineering from the Birla Institute of Technology & Science, India, a masters, also in engineering, from Purdue University and an MBA from the University of Chicago. 110.bio: Ron Zapar is CEO of Re-Quest, Inc., a reseller and services firm focused on Oracle database on premise and cloud solutions. Ron started his Oracle career in early 1988 when he joined Oracle Corp. in their consulting organization in the North Central region in Chicago, IL. In 1991 he left Oracle to start his first integration firm, Quest Consulting, Inc., centered on the Oracle database and development tools. He involved his company in Oracle Applications solutions in the Mid-90s, and Quest was an inaugural member of the Oracle Business Alliance Program, the first resale channel program created by Oracle Corp. Quest formed its Managed Services practice in 1998, creating a true 1-stop-shop for the Oracle customer. In 2000 Ron sold Quest, and in 2003 launched Re-Quest, Inc., focusing the company on Oracle software and cloud resale and Managed Services solutions. Re-Quest currently holds the position of OPN Specialized Gold Partner, is a Strategic Oracle Database Appliance partner, and is Specialized and Certified to resell Oracle's cloud solutions.

118.bio:
Mr. Dennen joined Solairus Aviation in 2011 and has extensive experience as a finance and operations executive in the aviation industry.  He has overall responsibility for Solairus’ financial and client accounting activities. 

He provides executive leadership in business metrics, process improvement and contract negotiations as well as having responsibility for client relationships and providing guidance to clients and their advisors on various business and tax aspects of aircraft ownership structures.   He was the executive sponsor for driving the Oracle Fusion platform to successful completion.  

Prior to Solairus, Mr. Dennen spent over 13 years as the Senior Vice President of Finance for TAG Aviation and its successor companies, managing business aviation fleets in excess of 200 aircraft; prior to that he worked for PricewaterhouseCoopers.  

Mr. Dennen has been a member of the National Business Aviation Association (NBAA) tax committee for over 15 years and has lectured at numerous aviation industry seminars. 

Mr. Dennen received an MBA from New York University’s Stern School of Business with a major in Finance and Management and a Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting from the University of Rhode Island.  He is also a Certified Public Accountant.

About Solairus Aviation
Solairus is a US-based private aviation services company whose core business is assisting aircraft owners with the safe, reliable, and efficient management and operation of their aircraft. Our services are customized to meet the client’s individual travel and financial requirements, and to support their flight operation with the highest standards of safety and personalized service, regardless of the location of the aircraft.
Solairus was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in the San Francisco Bay Area. Solairus has over 50 base locations nationwide, employing more than 400 flight crew and support personnel to operate a fleet currently numbering more than 150 aircraft. Solairus is an Aviation Research Group/US Platinum-Rated and Wyvern Wingman certified charter operator. Solairus has also received the NBAA Commercial Business Flying Safety Award and is an IS-BAO Stage Three certified company. Solairus offers a full range of services in addition to aircraft management, which includes aircraft charter sales, aviation support services, and consulting.

121.bio:
Jim Battenberg is Senior Director, IaaS Product Marketing at Oracle, where his focus spans the entire IaaS portfolio of services.

Jim’s time in “the cloud” dates back to the mid/late 90’s when the shared hosting, dedicated hosting and ASP markets first began implementing the core concepts of virtualization. He developed and launched a suite of profitable hosting services from scratch and helped take Interliant (later purchased by Navisite) public.  

Prior to Oracle, Jim led the Platform Enablement team for the CenturyLink Cloud. Before that he led marketing, and created the first product marketing function for the Rackspace Cloud. He has also held senior product management and marketing leadership roles at enterprise hardware, software and hosting companies across startups and Fortune 500 firms. Jim holds a Finance degree and an MBA from the University of Houston.  

Finally, Jim loves yoga, poker and dubstep and claims to be able to combine all 3 – but you’ll have to ask him to see it!

122.bio:
Ankur started his career as a technologist. He moved to a being a project manager and then into management and strategy consulting. He has worked in diverse industries, from Pharma, Insurance, Marketing and High Tech.

He brings a consulting-friendly, Business Relationship Management approach to IT organizations. He is currently managing diverse teams which straddle the cloud as well as traditional legacy applications. Over the last seven years he has successfully implemented and migrated large enterprise applications and ERP's. He has executed both Back-office and Front-office applications, like Oracle ERP as well as Salesforce.

He has created and led enterprise PMO's for medium and large companies. As a practitioner he has used traditional methodologies very effectively. Over the last decade he transitioned to Agile methodologies. He has successfully implemented Agile/Scrum in an enterprise roll-out. He promotes the concept of "start small" and change the culture in organizations. He deliberately works at building consensus with the CxO level as well as promoting a bottoms up,
servant-leadership model of decision making. He implements change management patterns which mirror technology adoption.
Ankur is a frequent speaker presenting his case studies in conferences like Dreamforce and Oracle Open World.

Ankur has lived and worked in local New England over the last two decades. He enjoys long /distance running and gardening.

124.bio:
Phil is the Director of Enterprise Applications for Arconic Inc., which was formerly named Alcoa Inc. prior to the carve-out of the Primary Metals division into a new company (named Alcoa Corp.) in November of 2016.  Arconic is a global company with dual headquarters in Pittsburgh and New York City, and manufactures light-metal based products (aluminum, titanium, cobalt, nickel) for the aerospace, defense, automotive, commercial transportation and building industries.  The company has approximately 150 locations, 41,500 employees and generates revenue of $13B annually.  Phil’s role includes support for systems in the Financial, Requisition-to-Pay, Order-to-Cash, Integration Services, HR, Data Analytics, Customer Experience, .com, and End-User Productivity areas.  Oracle eBusiness Suite and HCM SaaS are prominent among the applications supported by the Pittsburgh-based team.  

Prior to his current role, Phil held the following roles:
•	IS Director for Alcoa Power and Propulsion in Cleveland, OH from May 2009-July 2014
•	IS Director for the Alcoa Wheel and Transportation Products / Forged Products businesses in Cleveland, OH from 2000-2009 
•	IS Manager for the start-up of Alcoa’s European Financial Shared Services Center in Drunen, the Netherlands, 1997-2000   
•	Systems analyst / Project leadership roles in the corporate MIS organization from 1986-1996

A native of Ashland, Ohio, Phil graduated from The Ohio State University’s Fisher College of Business in 1986 with a bachelor’s degree in management information systems and finance and has an MBA from the Joseph M. Katz Graduate School of Business at the University of Pittsburgh.

130.bio:
Ashish Nadkarni
Group Vice President, Infrastructure Systems, Platforms and Technologies

Ashish Nadkarni is Group Vice President within IDC's worldwide infrastructure practice. He leads a team of analysts who engage in delivering qualitative and quantitative research on computing, storage, and data management infrastructure platforms and technologies, via syndicated research programs (subscription services), data products (IDC Trackers) and custom engagements. Ashish’s vision for his team is to take a holistic, forwarding-looking and long-term view on emerging as well as established infrastructure-related areas in the datacenter, in the cloud and at the edge. His core research starts with an objective assessment of heterogeneous, accelerated, fog, edge and quantum computing architectures, silicon, memory and data persistence technologies, composable and disaggregated systems, rackscale design, software-defined infrastructure, modern operating system environments, and physical, virtual and cloud computing software. It is complemented by research on current and next-gen applications and workloads, vertical and industry-specific use cases, emerging storage and server form factors and deployment models, and upcoming IT vendors. Ashish also takes a keen interest in tracking the ongoing influence of open and open-source communities like OpenStack and Open Compute Project on infrastructure.

In 2009, Brendan Logan joined Oracle’s Communications Global Business Unit (CGBU) as their Global Vice President, Oracle Communications Consulting. He leads this consulting organization, focused on ensuring the successful deployment and optimization of Oracle Communications and Media applications and technology by its clients. Brendan brings an accomplished track record in the industry.

In 1995, Brendan co-founded Logan-Orviss International with Colin Orviss after recognising a need for pragmatic, information systems focused advisory services to the communications industry.   

Brendan is a popular writer and commentator on the communications industry and has been widely published in many trade journals.  He has worked with Operators in over 30 countries on all continents, defining enterprise information systems architectures and managing the implementation of solutions as business change catalysts for his clients. His detailed understanding of the business and commercial implications of information systems deployment are routinely accessed by both the communications operators and software vendors to ensure that the business goals of both communities are aligned.

1974 -1989: A variety of roles culminating in becoming Head of Software Development at Telecom Ireland until 1989.

143.bio: Brendan Tierney, Oracle ACE Director, is an independent consultant (Oralytics) and lectures on data science, databases, and Big Data at the Dublin Institute of Technology/Dublin Technological University. He has 25+ years of experience working in the areas of data mining, data science, Big Data, and data warehousing. Brendan is a recognized data science and Big Data expert and has worked on projects in Ireland, the UK, Belgium, Holland, Norway, Spain, Canada, and the U.S. Brendan is active in the Oracle User Group community, where he is one of the leaders for the OUG in Ireland and is a Member Advocate at Board of Director level with the UKOUG. Brendan has also been editor of the UKOUG Oracle Scene magazine and is a regular speaker at conferences around the world. He is an active blogger and also writes articles for OTN, Oracle Scene, IOUG SELECT Journal, ODTUG Technical Journal, and ToadWorld. He is also on the board of directors for DAMA in Ireland. Brendan has published four books, three with Oracle Press/McGrwa-Hill (Predictive Analytics Using Oracle Data Miner, Oracle R Enterprise: Harnessing the Power of R in Oracle Database, and Real World SQL and PL/SQL: Advice from the Experts) and one with MIT Press (Essentials of Data Science). These books are available on Amazon and the Essentials of Data Science book, is available in April 2018. Web and blog: www.oralytics.com Twitter: @brendantierney
143.globalBio: Brendan Tierney, Oracle GroundBreaker Ambassador & Oracle ACE Director, is an independent consultant (Oralytics) and lectures on data science, databases, and Big Data at the Dublin Institute of Technology/Dublin Technological University. He has 25+ years of experience working in the areas of data mining, data science, Big Data, and data warehousing. Brendan is a recognized Data Science and Big Data expert and has worked on projects in Ireland, the UK, Belgium, Holland, Norway, Spain, Canada, and the U.S. Brendan is active in the Oracle User Group community, where he is one of the leaders for the OUG in Ireland and is a Member Advocate at Board of Director level with the UKOUG. Brendan has also been editor of the UKOUG Oracle Scene magazine and is a regular speaker at conferences around the world. He is an active blogger and also writes articles for OTN, Oracle Scene, IOUG SELECT Journal, ODTUG Technical Journal, and ToadWorld. He is also on the board of directors for DAMA in Ireland. Brendan has published four books, three with Oracle Press/McGrwa-Hill (Predictive Analytics Using Oracle Data Miner, Oracle R Enterprise: Harnessing the Power of R in Oracle Database, and Real World SQL and PL/SQL: Advice from the Experts) and one with MIT Press (Essentials of Data Science). These books are available on Amazon, in print, ebook and audio book formats. Web and blog: www.oralytics.com Twitter: @brendantierney
